The '''Hespori''' is a [[sporadic boss|sporadic]] [[Farming]] boss fought in the cave within the west wing of the [[Farming Guild]] which requires {{SCP|Farming|65|link=yes}} {{Boostable|yes}} to access. To fight the Hespori, you must first plant a [[hespori seed]] in the [[hespori patch]] within the cave, and then wait 22-32 hours for it to grow (depending on planting time). You will need a [[rake]] to clear the patch of any [[weeds]], and a [[seed dibber]] to plant the seed unless the Farming portion of [[Barbarian Training]] has been completed. The flower behind the cave entrance will bloom when the Hespori is ready to be fought.

Attempting to harvest the seed with a [[spade]] will awaken the Hespori. After killing it, the seed may be harvested granting 12,600 Farming [[experience]] (12,915 with full [[farmer's outfit]]) and a range of [[seeds]], including the rare [[white lily seed|white lily]] and [[anima seed]]s. There is also a 1/35 chance to drop the [[bottomless compost bucket]].

==Fight overview==

=== Mechanics ===
[[File:Fighting Hespori.png|left|thumb|220px|A player battles the Hespori.]]
[[File:Hespori dead.png|left|thumb|220px|A defeated Hespori.]]
The Hespori is surrounded by four [[Flower|flower buds]] that keep it invulnerable while it attacks the player. These buds open three times during the fight: on initiation of the fight, when the Hespori has 66%, and  when the Hespori has 33% health remaining. Each bud has 10 hitpoints but will die in one hit from any weapon.

The Hespori has a ranged attack, a magic attack, and a special attack:

'''Ranged Attack''':

Throws green spores that hit twice with a max hit of 8+8 (reduced to 2+2 with [[Protect from Missiles]]'')''.

'''Magic Attack:''' 

A green wave with a max hit of 14 (reduced to 3 with [[Protect from Magic]]).

'''Special Attack''': 

{{mes|color=red|Hespori entangles you in some vines!}} will appear in the chatbox when the Hespori uses this special attack, with roots immobilizing the player preventing movement and attacks. After 6 seconds (10 ticks) the player will take 40+ damage unless they break free early by clicking repeatedly on either a new tile or the Hespori, or by using a [[Transformation rings|Transformation Ring]]. As you click, {{mes|You feel the vines loosen slightly as you try to move.}} will appear in the chatbox and after the 5th such message, clicking again will prevent the special attack and allow the player to move and attack again.


===Setup/Strategy===
{{Main|Hespori/Strategies}}
Hespori has low slash Defence, making [[slash weapon]]s the best option. At least level 60 melee stats, a [[dragon scimitar]], and high Ranged defence or [[Strength bonus]] equipment is recommended. A special attack weapon such as a [[dragon dagger]] can be used to quickly deal damage.

For players with lower melee combat stats, a viable option is to use fire spells, as they will have double accuracy and damage due to Hespori's 100% weakness to this element. A minimum Magic level of 59 for Fire Blast, level 40 Prayer for [[Protect from Missiles]], and good magic attack gear such as [[Mystic robes]] or better are recommended, due to Hespori's high magical defence. 

Bring high healing food, [[antipoison]], melee stat [[boost]]s, and optionally a Ranged weapon, such as [[darts]] or a charged [[blowpipe]] to quickly kill Hespori's flowers. Some players may wish to save potions and instead catch one of the stat boosting butterflies outside the guild. A [[Prayer potion]] may be required if the fight lasts too long.

A [[hespori seed]], [[spade]], and [[seed dibber]] (if the Farming portion of [[Barbarian Training]] has not been completed) are required to plant a new Hespori after the previous Hespori has been defeated and dug up.

Before waking up the Hespori, [[boost]], get [[poison]] immunity and equip a Ranged weapon. With high Ranged Defence armour, turn on [[Protect from Magic]], otherwise use [[Protect from Missiles]] if using higher Magic Defence armour. Also use melee stat boosting [[Prayer]]s if available.

Wake up the Hespori, and attack the first round of flowers with Ranged. Swap to a [[special attack]] weapon and use the special attacks on Hespori. Switch back to the main slash weapon if the next round of flowers were not activated. Kill the flowers with ranged. If the fight lasts longer than 30-40 seconds, the player will be rooted in place and must escape the vines by clicking to move or attack 7 times. Attack the Hespori until the flowers are active again. Switch to Ranged and kill them again. Finish off Hespori.

Clear the Hespori patch to receive its drops.

==History==
According to [[Arno]], the Hespori is a rare carnivorous plant originating from [[Morytania]], becoming conscious and highly aggressive once fully grown. They were also used as a weapon against vampyres by [[Queen Efaritay]].{{CiteNPC|npc=Mysterious Stranger|quote=They were grown here back when this place was still known as Hallowvale. The Saradominist Queen of the region used them as weapons against the vampyres.}}  The Hespori's appearance is also extremely similar to that of [[The Maiden of Sugadinti]]; it has been confirmed that there is a link between the two.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1084257292709711872|date=13 January 2019|archiveurl=https://reldo.runescape.wiki/i/107461|archivedate=28 April 2020|quote=[The Hespori bears a striking resemblance to the Maiden from TOB. It's also a plant from Morytania. Is there a possible link between the two?] Yes :)}} This link is confirmed in the quest [[A Night at the Theatre]], in which it is revealed that the Maiden was created using Hespori bark, which possesses regenerative properties.{{CiteNPC|npc=Ranis Drakan|quote=When we created the Maiden, we experimented heavily in [regeneration]. [...] Well in the end it wasn't actually haemalchemy that gave us the answer. It came in the form of a gift from the old queen. [...] Specifically the hespori. Their bark has wonderful regenerative abilities.|loc=A Night at the Theatre}}

A [[Hespori (A Night at the Theatre)|harder version of the Hespori]] is fought during A Night at the Theatre quest.

